Germany's Merz Warns Trump On Ukraine Peace Plan Deadline For Zelensky | 'NO DEAL WITHOUT CONSENT' German Chancellor Friedrich Merz has made a clear and forceful statement to President Trump: Europe must be part of any process to end Russia’s war in Ukraine. During a lengthy call following the G20 summit, Merz stressed that peace cannot be negotiated over Ukraine’s head, and warned that a Ukrainian defeat would ripple across the entire continent. He also invoked the 1994 Budapest Memorandum—which offered Kyiv security guarantees in exchange for giving up its nuclear arsenal—and said that those assurances failed. Now, he insists new, reliable guarantees must be built into any deal. Watch for more details.
